{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 09:59:36.203146", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnostic Report\nNetwork: multi‑tier Clos (EBGP, FRR)\nDate: (current capture)\nScope: Hosts pc_0_0 ↔ pc_0_1 connectivity and overall control-plane / forwarding state\n\nExecutive summary\n- Observed end-to-end connectivity failure: pc_0_0 cannot reach pc_0_1 (100% packet loss).\n- The forwarding/routing plane on routers (leaf, spine, super‑spine) appears converged and has routes for both host /24s.\n- The immediate fault is at the host/link level for pc_0_1: its interface is administratively/down or otherwise down on the access link to leaf_router_0_1. This prevents ARP/host delivery and causes the \"Destination Host Unreachable\" responses seen from leaf_router_0_1.\n\nDetailed findings and evidence\n\n1) End-to-end symptom\n- From pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1:\n  - Ping result: 5 packets transmitted, 0 received, 100% packet loss.\n  - ICMP error: \"From 172.16.0.7 icmp_seq=X Destination Host Unreachable\"\n    - 172.16.0.7 is the leaf_router_0_1 inter-router address; that device is returning the ICMP unreachable.\n\n2) Host interface state (localization of fault)\n- pc_0_1 network config:\n  - ifconfig shows eth0 with flags=4098 (BROADCAST,MULTICAST) — interface state DOWN (not UP).\n  - ip_addr output: eth0 present with 10.0.1.2/24 but the interface is DOWN.\n  - ifconfig also shows RX packets 0, TX packets 0 and RX errors/dropped counters (dropped 9).\n- leaf_router_0_1 -> pc_0_1:\n  - Ping from leaf_router_0_1 to 10.0.1.2 returns \"From 10.0.1.1 Destination Host Unreachable\" (100% loss).\n  - leaf_router_0_1 eth2 is configured 10.0.1.1/24 and is UP; it cannot reach the host IP — consistent with the host NIC/link being down.\n\nInterpretation: The access interface on pc_0_1 is administratively down OR the physical/link layer between pc_0_1 and leaf_router_0_1 is down. The leaf interface (10.0.1.1) is up and can transmit, but there is no L2/L1 response from the host.\n\n3) Router control-plane/route state (what is working)\n- leaf_router_0_0:\n  - eth2 10.0.0.1/24 (UP). IP route contains 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (BGP next hop) — indicates leaf_router_0_0 learned route for 10.0.1.0/24 via the fabric.\n- leaf_router_0_1:\n  - eth2 10.0.1.1/24 (UP). IP route contains 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (BGP next hop).\n- spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1:\n  - Both have ethX addresses in 172.16.0.x/31 and routing entries pointing to 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via next-hops in the fabric (entries show proto bgp).\n- super_spine_router_0:\n  - Shows 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 routes via 172.16.0.1 (proto bgp).\n- Net effect: BGP-advertised host prefixes are present in router routing tables with expected next-hops. The inter-router fabric and EBGP appear to be exchanging routes correctly.\n\n4) Why ICMP unreachable source IP differs\n- The ICMP \"Destination Host Unreachable\" messages seen by pc_0_0 are sourced from 172.16.0.7 (leaf_router_0_1's fabric-facing address). That happens because a packet is forwarded across the fabric toward leaf_router_0_1; the leaf receives the packet but cannot deliver it to the final host on its connected subnet, so it generates the ICMP unreachable using the source IP of the interface that received the packet (the fabric interface), hence 172.16.0.7.\n\nImpact\n- Host-level connectivity to pc_0_1 is down (pc_0_1 unreachable from within the pod and from other pods).\n- Router-level routing and EBGP appear healthy; reachability to the prefix 10.0.1.0/24 is present in the routing table but the last hop (host/link) is not reachable.\n\nRoot cause (most likely)\n- pc_0_1 local interface is down (administrative or L1/L2 failure) or cable/link to leaf_router_0_1 is down. Evidence: pc_0_1 eth0 state = DOWN in ip/link output and leaf_router_0_1 cannot ARP/reach 10.0.1.2.\n\nAdditional evidence (selected extracts)\n- pc_0_1 ip_addr snippet: \"eth0: <BROADCAST,MULTICAST> ... inet 10.0.1.2/24 ... state DOWN\"\n- leaf_router_0_1 ifconfig/eth2: \"inet 10.0.1.1/24 ... RX packets 0 ... TX packets 9\"\n- ping results:\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: \"From 172.16.0.7 icmp_seq=X Destination Host Unreachable\"\n  - leaf_router_0_1 -> pc_0_1: \"From 10.0.1.1 Destination Host Unreachable\"\n- Router ip_route outputs show mutual reachability of prefixes via BGP next-hops (10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 present across routers).\n\nSummary conclusion\n- Network control plane (EBGP/FRR across leaf/spine/super‑spine) is functioning and prefixes are propagated.\n- The outage is localized to the access host/link for pc_0_1 (host NIC/interface is down or link disconnected).\n- This is a last-hop (L1/L2 or host administrative) failure — routers can route to the host prefix, but the host itself is not reachable on the physical/subnet link.\n\nIf you want, I can run additional checks (BGP neighbor/status on FRR, ip link on pc_0_1, ARP tables on leaf_router_0_1, or switch/simulated link diagnostics) to further validate or narrow whether the problem is administrative-down vs physical cable/link. (No remediation steps applied unless you request them.)", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10267, "output_tokens": 2821, "total_tokens": 13088, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9856}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1344}}}
